http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Nava-Nirmana-Samithi-founder-mourned/article14011731.ece

Forum for Development of North Andhra Chairman K.V. Ramana has mourned the death of Visakha district Nava Nirmana Samithi founder A.L. Narasimha Murthy.Mr Ramana said Mr. Narasimha Murthy did laudable work in areas of health, education, food security, water supply and harvesting, maternal land child health in collaboration with 25 national and international organisationsTo work for the uplift of villages particularly Girijans, the samithi was formed at Visakhapatnam in 1972 and was later shifted to Narsipatnam, the gateway to the Agency, in 1980.